==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: sĭk
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /sɪk/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /sIk/
*{{audio|en-us-sick.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪk|-ɪk]]
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[sēoc]]''
====Homophones====
*[[sic]]

===Adjective===
'''sick'''  ({{compar}}: '''[[sicker]]''', {{superl}}: '''[[sickest]]''')

# In poor health 
# (''colloquial'') Mentally unstable, disturbed.
# (''colloquial'') In bad taste.
#:''That's a sick joke.''
# {{cattag|slang}} very good, excellent
# In poor condition 
#: ''(sick building syndrome; my car is looking pretty sick; my job prospects are pretty sick)''

====Synonyms====
*(''in poor health''): [[ill]], not [[well]], [[poorly]] (''British''), [[sickly]], [[unwell]]
*(''mentally unstable''): [[disturbed]], [[sick in the head]], [[twisted]], [[warped]].
*(''slang: excellent''): [[cool]], [[rad]], [[wicked]]

====Antonyms====
*(''in poor health'') [[fit]], [[healthy]], [[well]]
*(''slang: excellent''): [[crap]], [[naff]], [[uncool]]

====Idioms====
#:[[sick as a dog]] - in poor health

